import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    state_counts = data.groupby('state').count().reset_index()
    gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(state_counts, geometry='geometry')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    gdf.plot(column='count', cmap='coolwarm', legend=True, edgecolor='black')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of cities across different states?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'])
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude values?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts().head(10)
    city_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the most common city name in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['city_population'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('City Population')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities based on their population?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], marker='o', label='City locations')
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the spatial distribution of cities in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
